						<summary>

						<p>On a stone near the Tirumalarāya temple on the hill near the village.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1558 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 14[80], Kāḷayukti, Āsvīja śu. 1,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1558 A.D., September 13, (Tuesday).</hi></p>						

						<p>The name of the king and the date only can be read. The rest of the record is very much damaged.</p>						

